Members of the Welsh Assembly do not want to “look like muppets”
Among some members of the National Assembly, there is a growing dissatisfaction with the proposal to adopt the abbreviation MWP (Member of the Welsh Parliament - a member of the Parliament of Wales) for their name.
The problematic solution is related to plans to change the name of the Assembly to the Parliament of Wales.
Members of the Assembly from different political parties are concerned about possible jokes with this abbreviation.
One Labour member, expressing his party’s opinion, expressed concern that the new abbreviation “rhymes Twp and Pwp”.
For our readers not from Wales: in Welsh twp means "dumb", and pwp - "duck".
According to a member of the Assembly from the Party of Wales, his organization as a whole “remained dissatisfied” and offered other options.
Representatives of the conservative party “do not object” to the new abbreviation, but note that MWP is close in writing to the word Muppet (muppet).
In this context, the letter w in Welsh is pronounced roughly like the letter u in the Yorkshire dialect of English.
The Assembly Committee, which is currently drafting a draft law on renaming, made the following statement: “The final decision on the names of the Members of the Assembly will, of course, remain with them”.
The Wales Governance Act of 2017 authorizes the National Assembly of Wales to change its name.
In June, the Committee published the results of a public opinion poll on the proposed options, according to which the option “Parliament of Wales” instead of “Assembly” found wide support among the local population.
As for the name of the members of the Assembly, the Committee expressed a preference for the Welsh Parliament Members (WMP) option, while the MWP option received the most public support.
The members of the Assembly seemed to offer other options, but it would not be easy for the Presiding Member, Elin Jones, to find a solution that would suit everyone.
The reform laws will include other modifications to the Assembly ' s working process, including new rules on disqualification of members of the Assembly and the organization of the Committee ' s system.
Members of the Assembly will vote on the final version of their name during the debate on the bill.
